The tenant of Bakal: The stoves are heating, he signed a higher rent.
An imposing elderly man walked out the door of the RPG Byty customer center of the "coal baron" Zdenek Bakal, the largest private owner of apartments for rent in the Czech Republic.
He was carrying under his arm a file with three new leases for three apartments: his own, that of his daughter and that of his son who is serving a sentence.
Deregulation has increased the rent for these three people.
Instead of paying 3500 the son will have to pay from next year for a 2+1 apartment of second category 4100 crowns.
"And there's no hot water and the heating works on solid fuel," he said of his son's new contract, the man with the signature power.
“But I signed it anyway,” he said, moaning in anger and half-resigned.
The citizen association of apartments BytyOKD.cz, which described the new rental conditions as "immoral and indecent", advises tenants not to sign and wait until December 7, when a notice will be published explaining the method to follow to claim.
But the man reacts to this with a gesture of the hand.
"One says this, the other says something else" frowning.
The Ostrava region becomes the laboratory of deregulation.
After the New Year, this is what most apartments in the Czech Republic expect, whose rents do not correspond to the market price.
Aktualne.cz has therefore decided to personally visit the "laboratory".
The RPG waiting room in Havirovska Street is one of four in the Ostrava region and is already full on Tuesday at 9am.
Right next to the door stands a security company guard with a device to call customers.
A special button, "rent 2011", is lit on the touch screen.
A single press and a paper with a number comes out of the device.
You don't have time to read your number "157" as your number is already starting to light up on the big screen under the top of the waiting room.
In a fraction of a second, it's your turn.
After a brief moment, an old couple arrives to inquire about the rent, but the new rents do not seem to concern people in the waiting room.
The majority of people have come to solve common problems like everywhere else - claim for repairs, insurance-related events and so on.
In the Ostrava region, people from more than 44,000 apartments in the RPG portfolio have been receiving letters with new leases in their mailbox since about mid-November.
RPG Byty offers them rent increases of 15 to 38 percent.
The special rental counter has been open to the public since 18 November.
"it has been working for almost a week, so it's still on trial," the employee responds, after a moment of hesitation, behind the counter when the client presents himself as a journalist.
Deragulation and the former miner's apartments in Bakal are a very sensitive local topic.
The vice-president of the parliament and from the region of Ostrava Lubomir Zaoralek of the Social Democrats reported this fairly strongly before the elections and it now fills the local newspapers.
“Twenty years after them, I want a new floor.”
"They didn't even change me a put...n board in the toilet, relieves in the introduction the man mentioned.
However, it is mostly, according to employees, retirees who come to be sure that they will receive a discount on the new rent price if they sign now as promised in a special offer.
This is a rebate of half the amount of the rent that the other tenants who will have signed their new contract before December 15 will receive.
But the "deregulation" window on Havirovaska Street is really not overwhelmed by questions.
“Of the 360 customers who came yesterday, only 40 to 50 came for rent,” the employee says at the counter.
And yet RPG puts up both on its website and in the windows individual interviews on rents when necessary.
If the two parties do not agree on the rent, an independent court will make the decision.
“It’s not about threats, it’s just about informing about the unique and legitimate way to act legally,” RPG said on its website.
“No one will go to court here,” thinks one of RPG Byty’s employees and the man in the street in front of the customer center gives her reason.
“I have 13,000 retirement crowns and I have 5,000 crowns left to eat, I don’t have enough to go to court,” he says.
The employee suddenly feels uneasy.
"We'll see."
"Mr. Zaoralek in the media asks that no one sign and therefore people wait," she said.
Rent regulation ends in the Czech Republic with the beginning of 2011 and increases, according to RPG Byty, are an economic necessity.
“Moreover, the current rents still do not reach the level necessary for the simple maintenance of the housing fund,” recalls Pavel Klimes, director of the residential portfolio of the company RPG Byty, that it is precisely the negligence of the fund for housing that makes the tenant angry is the main reason for the increase in rent.
However in 5 years between 2005 and 2010 RPG was able to invest with rents in apartments 4 billion, in four years from 2011 to 2014 it should make 5.2 billion.
The large screen hanging from the ceiling in front of the upholstered armchairs of the waiting room on Havirosvka Street, however, repeats some information indicated in red.
"The rent increase in 2011 is 15 percent and concerns no less than 31,200 apartments or more than 90 percent of RPG apartments."
"And it will always be at most 7.50 Czech crowns per m2 per month," the screen says.
The 38 percent increase concerns only 400 apartments in the RPG portfolio.
“In these cases, it’s a really very low increase of 19.66 Czech crowns per m2,” adds RPG.
Next year the rent will remain the same for 2600 apartments.
RPG Byty promises that deregulation will not cause a radical but gradual increase over 4 to 8 years.
It adds other commitments: all the money from the rent increase (see graph) is returned to the apartments in the form of heating savings - new windows and heating.
Those who sign the rent increase agreement have priority.
The kindergarten is also part of the offices included the architects.
The Avriopoint administrative building in Brno is the new headquarters of Arch. Design.
No one could have expected it to also house a mini kindergarten with everything you need - colorful walls, imaginative furniture, toys and finally a miniature playground on the terrace.
Since October last year, the children of Arch. design employees can go there.
Architectural project company Arch. Design., whose workshops have produced a large number of buildings in Brno, has designed its mini business kindergarten since the first drafts of the Avriopoint building.
She employs about 90 people, mostly of child-bearing age, and she was concerned that women architects and project managers could quickly get back to work.
At the same time as reduced-time contracts, kindergarten is a bonus offered to its employees by Arch. Design. as part of its social program.
Builders and architects have the opportunity to combine work taking care of children.
It was the employees of Arch.Design themselves who conceived this kindergarten and with the support of management they were able to obtain an endowment from the European Union and the Ministry of Labour and Social Affairs.
The mini kindergarten is financed by the European Social Fund through the Human Resources Operational Programme and the State Budget of the Czech Republic.
They were able to purchase equipment and appliances and after two years to provide qualified personnel as well as start-up.
After the use of the funding endowment (two years) the company Arch. Design. has the obligation after 3 years to operate the mini kindergarten on its own funds.
The preparation of the project lasted one year and it was the company Economy rating that helped to make the application for staffing.
Children's care is provided by a qualified staff, all day a nurse and a kindergarten teacher take care of the children. children can go to kindergarten without age limitation but they are over three years for the most part.
As it is a "mini kindergarten" there can be only 5 children present at the same time, but during the day there are more who replace each other.
The operation of the school is flexible according to the needs of the parents and the children of all employees have the same right to use this school without regard to the hierarchical position.
Although it is an individual care and education, the curriculum of the mini-kindergarten is comparable to that for pre-school education.
The children do not only play, but quality education is also provided - from the beginning until the preparation at the school benches, English is taught.
The classroom is equipped not only with imaginative toys and games but also with a computer that children can use.
The presence of small children in society creates a friendly and positive environment.
Parents can at any time control their child and not have the stress of a delay to pick up the children in a school far from the parents' workplace.
Parents use their time in the most productive way.
It is not surprising that a natural relationship of loyalty is created between the employee and the employer.
Arch.Design.s is thus registered among the companies that offer a bonus of choice for the recruitment of new employees and that are friendly to the family and through this program strengthens HR marketing.
The bone house still fascinates after 100 years. Take a look at Gaudi’s interiors.
The roof resembles the back of a prehistoric saurian, the staircase has a dinosaur spine and the balconies have open fish mouths.
This is how the Casa Battlo house in Barcelona was built by the architect Antoni Gaudi.
Due to its organic shapes, the house has received from the locals the nickname of Maison en os.
Organic shapes, wild colors, unusual use of stones, fragments of tiles and mosaic, fa<0xC3><0xA7>ade reminiscent of scales and everywhere present curves, this is all that is epic for the Art Nouveau of Antoni Gaudi.
The front fa<0xC3><0xA7>ade of the house unfolds its dreamy lines, its pleasant colors and textures that recall nature and animals.
In the course of a more detailed observation we see the geometry, the rhythm and the order thought with precision.
In the night the facade of the house becomes even more dramatic and is lit in such a way that the impression of brightness of colors is reinforced.
The winding and twisting of the shapes also appears in the interiors with the same measure.
The wood copies in waves the window frames, the balustrades, the decorative elements of the doors, the eyelet and the slats.
The Battlo house that stands in the Eixample district in the shopping street Passeig de Gracia at number 43, was born from the construction of an 1877 house by the architect Emilio Sala Cortes.
The reconstruction took two years and the house was completed in 1906.
The investor, Joseph Battlo, a wealthy entrepreneur, first insisted on demolishing the old building and building a brand new one, but quickly accepted Gaudi's idea of an unusual and cheaper reconstruction.
But the idea of Casa Battlo as a house with multiple dwellings was not conceived by Gaudi alone.
The architect Josep Maria Jujol worked with him.
It is precisely on his project that the decorations for a representative apartment of the owner of the building and the use of mosaic for the facade were born.
For the fa<0xC3><0xA7>ade also worked other artists and creators.
The joint work for the Casa Battlo house plans began with a successful cooperation between Jujol and Gaudi.
Jujol participated in the construction of Gaudi's Casa Mila and the Guell Park in which there are other works by Gaudi.
The locals dubbed the house hot right after it was finished because of its organic shapes "the House in Bone".
Others, in view of the specific mechanism of opening the windows have called it "the house that swings".
It is said that at the top of the construction there is a sword similar to that of St. George the patron of Catalonia.
Other sculptural elements of the construction contain hidden religious motifs.
Gaudi thought for the house a unique system in its central heating time, with ventilation vents and typical fireplaces.
Their inclination of 45 degrees seems odd.
During the creation Gaudi absolutely did not respect the construction guidelines of the time and did not allow himself to be hindered by them.
At the beginning of the construction he obtained the building permit from the city, knowing, of course, that the data carried on the reconstruction plans were so vague that two years later during the finish the city council was horrified and asked for modifications.
For example, the members of the municipal council did not like that the pillars of the construction started on the public sidewalk.
There was never any change, but, on the contrary, only 15 days after the city's call Josep Battlo asked (and obtained satisfaction) permission to rent the two highest floors.
The owner moved to the lower floors.
In the gallery on the second floor there was a common living room and on the third a bedroom and a private part of the apartment.
The ground floor was rented to a jewellery store.
The entire six-storey house is shared by a staircase through which one accesses to an independent roof terrace.
All right angles and straight lines were cancelled by the basic elements of the reconstruction and replaced by curved walls.
Gaudi also worked on the modern concept of linking spaces.
The common part can be connected completely by opening the doors of the salons and the high society can communicate comfortably or otherwise limit the private space for more intimate interviews.
The house with the reconstruction of Gaudi has received in addition to new facades a non-traditional roof and two more floors.
Gaudi’s play with light is also impressive, with blue and white glazed tiles with which the inner courtyard is decorated and with skylights.
The two-color game gives maximum light in all floors of the house.
It was enough simply to bet on the principle that white reflects more than the dark which, on the contrary, absorbs the rays of the sun.
The Casa Battlo house that was inscribed in 2005 in the UNESCO World Heritage Fund can be visited by everyone.
On the first floor of the house is the most spacious and splendid apartment accessible to the public.
The owners decided to take this step in 2002 on the occasion of the 150th anniversary of the birth of the famous designer.
They continued the visits because they found it to be a lucrative business and expanded the field of visits to the common areas and attic including roof terraces.
The entrance ticket to the monument is really cheap and costs 16.50 euros; students, retirees, groups and tourist card holders have 20 percent discount.
The sum is still above the entrance price to Gaudi's other buildings in the city.
If you want to feel the real atmosphere of the house with its fantastic turrets, you must quickly find a comrade among the inhabitants of the building and completely visit the house.
How to choose a mattress and a bed base: women have other criteria than men.
No ostentatious frame, but rather the quality of the surface reserved for the bed, so the mattress and bed base give a real basis for a good bed.
They must of course complement each other harmoniously to please a specific user.
During the choice several things are decisive,: the weight, the size, the age, the state of health as well as the sex of the owner.
The type of interior in which the mattress and bed base will be placed is also important.
A typical example?
For example in the country house where you do not sleep continuously latex mattresses are not appropriate because they "warm up" gently.
They also have a higher weight than standard polyurethane mattresses.
It is necessary to return them frequently.
If they do not also have enough ventilation channels in the heart and if they remain, in addition, on a solid board, they retain moisture. Mold can also form there.
Habit is also decisive in choice.
Anyone who spends the day abroad, where very thick mattresses with a softening layer are frequently used, will hardly feel good on a low, hard surface.
“That’s how all the hockey players who come back from the NHL complain that they can’t sleep there.”
“For their tired shoulders, feet and ribs, they needed mattresses with a softening layer of lazy foam.”
"Such mattresses are also recommended for people who suffer from diabetes who have a nervous system disorder that therefore misunderstand the "information" of the joints and skin," explains Sylva Adamczikova who specializes in upholstered furniture.
This is why a few years ago the mattress with lazy foam conquered the hockey players as well as other customers.
"Today everything is going well, Tempur, the Italian Magnifex but also the Czech Tropico have suitable mattresses for example.
You don't have to be an NHL guy to enjoy a lazy foam.
This “miracle” simply works.
It optimizes its rigidity and shape according to the heat absorbed or adapts to the heat of your body.
Nothing puts pressure on you and you won’t turn around in the night like after a tough game.
You just sleep better.
The lazy foam also works as a protection against squaring.
For the choice of the mattress according to your size, add the length of the feet, i.e. about 21/34 cm.
A man and a woman with a height of 180cm therefore need a bed of 210/220 cm.
The minimum width for each for a two-seater bed should be 90 cm or 180 cm in total.
For single beds, for example singles, it is recommended to take at least 120 /140 cm.
It is convenient in case of a visit.
'However there is a simple rule for the width of the bed: when you are lying on the back you should lay your hands comfortably with the elbows slightly bent. Helena Prokopova, President of the Association of Mattress-Butterliers and Decorators who has been dedicated for several years to the problem of healthy sleep and ergonomics of furniture and teaching in specialized schools.
For a two-seater bed each needs its own bed base and mattress, so be careful however during the checkout to choose the height of the mattress.
Otherwise you will only have to mount the bed base at different heights and this is not achievable on all bed frames.
Foam mattresses should have a minimum height of 14 cm, spring mattresses at least 15 cm, of this count for the layer of form and ventilation at least three centimeters.
"When touching or sitting on the mattress you should not feel the springs," warns Helena Prokopova.
Each mattress requires a well-determined type of mattress.
The bunk bed, when the mattress and the bunk bed are united like Siamese sisters, has nothing to do in the bedrooms.
The mattresses are very badly aired; it should not be washed, which is commonly done today.
And since during the night one normally sweats 0.2 to 0.75 l of sweat it is clear that after 5/7 years, the mattress begins to recall a large (and clogged) sieve.
For this reason, specialists refuse to advertise over a lifespan of 25 years for a mattress or a lifetime warranty.
But everything to his but.
And for this advice of experience from the sellers: for a mattress of 120/140cm, give up, for the covering of the mattress, hygiene or washing but rather add a protective mattress thatyou can easily remove and wash.
And even if nowadays it is common to manufacture coatings with zipper for the whole, that is to say that after opening we have two parts (for washing and the size of the washing machine is very important!) otherwise the handling for large models (and for one person) becomes when they are removed a fight between a light weight and a heavy weight on a ring.
Do you have a rigid board in your bed instead of a bed base?
Never! Never!
Maximum for a bed intended for visitors for one night only.
However, equip the board (if there are none) with ventilation holes and use the spring mattress with a minimum height of 15cm with pocket springs (from Germany Taschenfederken) and a layer of ventilation.
A polyurethane mattress should not be part of a bed of this type.
For single-position slatted mattresses with 14/18 slats, latex mattresses or so-called sandwiches (perhaps the combination of latex and coconut), are ideal but it will always be better for you to have a mattress with more slats, 28 and above, where the slats are doubled in the part of the bass and kidneys.
For mattresses with multiple positions, it is not necessary to take a spring mattress because it does not respond to changes in position.
In addition to adjusting the rigidity of the slats, a so-called shoulder cradle can also be installed.
This is a special connection of the slats that allows the slat to be pressed or even tilted so that the shoulder of the sleeper "fits in" well.
For men who have “shoulders as wide as their backs,” this is really an important thing.
This is already being considered by mattress manufacturers who for the "male" have begun to use a softening area at the level of the shoulders.
But they also think about women - they again offer them a softer surface at the hips.
For the most difficult customer there are wing or plate bed bases with what is called a multiforce suspension.
The pressure spreads to more points and dilutes the tension.
But of course, be careful, as soon as you use a bad pillow (large and inflated with air) on good mattresses and bed base, the "plus" disappears.
The basic rule is a simple pillow: the pillow should support the head and its tips should only reach the shoulders, so that the shoulder muscles can rest.
The recommended size is 50X60 cm that the Scandinavians prefer.
When lying on the side, the pillow should level (with the shoulder cradle of the bed base or the rammollie area in the mattress) the height of the shoulders.
Modern mattresses still have something in common with the first straw-based and herbal mattresses.
Manufacturers still use natural materials or mixtures.
The trend is also to the organic mattress.
Petroleum-based raw materials, from which polyurethane is made, are replaced by natural oils, such as soybean oil.
Almost all known manufacturers use soybeans.
“The Bio label for mattresses means that the heart is made from natural products,” explains Petr vasicek from Tropico Plus.
Natural materials are also used for mattress coatings; one of the first was aloe vera.
But you can add micro-capsules that develop scents of the forest or lavender.
There are differences between man and woman.
While birch plant extract for the mattress coating absorbs heat and cools the body, "cools" the man, the coatings "warms" women.
Red pepper extract accelerates blood circulation and is therefore warmer for the weaker sex.
The current favorites?
Mattresses made from cold foam (it has more pores with a disturbed cellular structure therefore more breathable than standard polyurethane and has more elasticity.
The combination of different stiffness of cold foams gives polyzone mattresses that know precisely where the head, lower back and feet are located.
You will pay for a quality mattress from 7,000 crowns and more.
Those who are characterized by their health parameters have less VAT and are taken as instruments for health.
In the Czech Republic, Gumotex took first place.
Saving for the mattress and bed base is not easy.
From time to time we may have as part of special actions from manufacturers or producers two mattresses for the price of one.
For example, the company Magniflex offers Duofreeze mattresses with memory foam sewn to the coating for 11990 crowns.
Of course, you can take the second one for free.
The era of lazy or viscoelastic foams with an open cell structure and a large thickness was started with Tempur material at a "cosmic" rate.
This started as a matter for NASA because astronauts were undergoing enormous charge factors at the start.
Tempur softens in the heat and hardens, on the contrary, in the cold.
It therefore adapts perfectly to the warm human body and distributes optimal pressure to it.
It is therefore ideal against bad sleep and for an increase in comfort during sleep.
Viscoelastic foams are used not only for mattresses but also for health products, such as special foot cushions that relieve the legs and the venous system.
Czech manufacturers use for example EucathermC or Twinsaver foam or the same type.
Devices to track people are increasingly in demand by parents who want to monitor their children.
Fear of their child leads more and more people to think about monitoring them through a GPS.
The system, set up at the beginning to search for cars can equally well be used to trace the movement of people and help in some cases such as that of the little Anicka Janatkova.
The instrument is currently as big as a matchbox but will soon be the size of a watch.
The case of little Anicka moved a large number of people and they began to look for ways to better protect their children.
Even if the price is to disturb their privacy.
“We strive to tell everyone that this is not espionage but just another way to lessen the likelihood of another tragedy,” says Petr Pilin of MAcro Weil, which is one of the providers of tracking devices in the Czech market.
"I admit that there may be cases of misuse of such devices, such as putting it in the bag of a person who is not aware, but I have not yet encountered such cases."
“The majority of people are customers who actually buy the product for safety reasons,” Pilin adds.
According to him, children should always know what purpose "the box" is used for and how to use it in an emergency.
Child psychologist Dana Bockova points out that if the child does not want to wear something like this, he will get rid of it.
“And even the little ones can show great creativity when it comes to purposely getting rid of something when they don’t want to be under control.”
“Mobile phones, which can be cut off like these tracking devices, have already led parents to long waits,” says Bockova.
According to her, the fact that this type of device can help in case of aggression is very questionable.
"If this is a prepared abduction, the perpetrator will do everything to ensure that the child does not have an electronic device that can locate him."
“Currently, it’s the phone.”
"As soon as the tracking devices are developed, they (criminals) will also be looking for them because the sale will be supported by an advertising campaign."
“In such cases, criminals will always be ahead of the police,” she said.
She admits, however, that such devices can help in an unprepared assault by a pedophile.
According to Robert Cech of RC Monitoring, which offers tracking services for both cars and people, having this type of device can help, even if it is destroyed in the event of an assault.
"The device can be configured in such a way that it is in regular emission after a certain period of time."
“In the event that the device is destroyed, it still remains the last position of the person concerned.”
"The more expensive devices also have an inclinometer that immediately signals the position of the person who slipped and finds himself in the lying position without moving," Cech says.
According to him, so-called smart mobile phones that are equipped with a navigation system, can offer a comparable service after having formatted it with a special software.
The problem with current tracking systems is that it is either a device similar to those worn as a matchbox-sized pendant or smaller telephone devices.
We can always lose them.
According to Pilina of the company Macro Weil, this is why tests are currently being carried out to make devices that look like common digital watches.
“This will have the advantage that the potential aggressor will not be able to recognize the tracking device.”
“Or he’ll figure it out after a while, which will give the police a little more time,” he added.
Whether the tracking device is developed in the form of a bracelet or pendant, it will always use the same technology as for tracking cars.
It is a combination of position acquisition systems by means of GPS (which is commonly used in auto-navigation) and a function of a mobile phone that alerts the current position of a vehicle.
The army has so many detonating strings that it could go around the Czech Republic with it, but it can only last two years.
