I hope that the current turbulence will bring us greater tranquility.
And that we can seize the opportunity that we have been given, until the spring of 2013.
It seems that President Zapatero also heard it this way and his double declaration (the reforms promised after the meeting last Saturday with big companies and yesterday's announcement of new measures) suggests that, despite Merkel's criticisms, the path has been paved for the thesis that it is necessary to put order at home.
But the red line that Germany has drawn is there, and they don't seem to move it.
And among the possibilities envisaged, it is not possible to exclude that of abandoning a monetary zone too full of insignificant countries.
